steps: How to Deploy React.js application on aws ubuntu server :-->
step 1) sudo apt update
        sudo apt upgrade -y

step 2) sudo apt install -y nodejs npm
        node --version
        npm --version

step 3) apt install git -y

step 4) git clone https://github.com/aadinathtighare/react-calculator.vercel.git

step 5) cd react-calculator.vercel/

step 6) npm install
        npm run build

step 7) Serve the React App:-->
If you are not using a web server, you can use a process manager like PM2 to keep your Node.js app running in the background:-->

      npm install -g pm2
      pm2 start npm --name App.js -- start

step 8) npm install -g serve
serve package : is a simple, zero-configuration command-line tool for serving static files, including those generated by React's build process.

step 9) pm2 serve build 80 --spa 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
build = folder
80 = port number
spa = Single Page Application (SPA) 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
pm2 = This is the command for managing Node.js processes using PM2.

serve = This is a built-in PM2 command for serving static files.
